was examined in 39 incidences, Sex or Gender 29 times, Income 17 instances, 
Geography 10 instances, and Education Level 3 instances. Occupation Status 2 
instances, and LGBTQ+ 0 times. Important disparities exist regarding CABG access 
and outcomes, especially involving members of the LGBTQ+, Native American, and 
Black communities. Further research is needed to address health disparities and 
their root causes for focused action and improved health of minoritized groups.

